<item>
            <title>[MNG-2365] classes before test-classes in MavenProject.getTestClasspathElements() - should be the other way around?</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-2365</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in getTestClasspathElements() we have:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        List list = new ArrayList( getArtifacts().size() + 1 );&lt;br/&gt;
        list.add( getBuild().getOutputDirectory() );&lt;br/&gt;
        list.add( getBuild().getTestOutputDirectory() );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;causing classes to be prior to test-classes in the classpath- something then prohibits test-resources/classes to shadow classes/ resources fom main. .I.e. it is not possible to redefine resources/classes for usage when running tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Sugested solution:&lt;br/&gt;
        List list = new ArrayList( getArtifacts().size() + 1 );&lt;br/&gt;
        list.add( getBuild().getTestOutputDirectory() );&lt;br/&gt;
        list.add( getBuild().getOutputDirectory() );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;add test-classes before classes&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>doesnt matter</environment>
